NOTICE TO USERS

The Traceable Provenance Open License (TPOL) is a copyleft open-source-oriented license focused on software provenance, attribution, transparency, and traceability.

This draft license is intended to:

preserve software freedom;

require publication of modified network services;

preserve attribution and provenance information;

encourage machine-readable traceability;

improve transparency of generated outputs and derived systems.


This license draft has not been reviewed or approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).


