1. DEFINITIONS

For the purposes of this Agreement, the following terms shall have the meanings set forth below:

(a) "Licensor" means each copyright holder who owns copyright or other applicable rights in the Work and who makes the Work available under this Agreement.

(b) "Licensee" means any individual or legal entity exercising rights granted under this Agreement.

(c) "Project" means the open-source software project through which the Work is made available.

(d) "Project Maintainer" means the individual(s) or entity publicly designated by the Project as responsible for maintaining the Project repository. The Project Maintainer may administer the Project, but does not receive authority to revoke rights already granted under this Agreement except as expressly provided herein.

(e) "Work" means the copyrightable files created by project developers and made available under this Agreement, including source code, documentation, configuration files, build scripts, images, examples, and other materials stored in the Project repository. The Work excludes third-party dependencies, libraries, assets, or materials that are governed by their own separate licenses.

(f) "Modified Work" means any modification, adaptation, translation, transformation, derivative work, or other work based upon the Work, to the extent recognized by applicable copyright law.

(g) "Covered Work" means the Work, any Modified Work, and any work that incorporates or is based on the Work in a manner that creates a derivative work under applicable copyright law.

(h) "Corresponding Source" means all source code, build scripts, configuration files, interface definitions, installation instructions, and other materials reasonably necessary to build, install, run, modify, and reproduce the Covered Work from source form.

(i) "Output" means files, data, content, or results generated by running, executing, compiling, processing, or otherwise using the Work or a Covered Work.

(j) "Licensee Input" means data, prompts, files, text, images, audio, video, code, configuration, business data, personal data, confidential information, or other materials supplied by Licensee or Licensee's users to or through the Work.

(k) "Attribution Notice" means a reasonably visible or machine-readable notice identifying the Project, the original author or organization if provided by the Project, the source repository URL, and a reference or link to this Agreement.


