2. OWNERSHIP OF OUTPUT AND INPUT

(a) No Ownership Claim Over Output. Except for portions of Output that reproduce, contain, or constitute a derivative work of the Work, Licensor claims no ownership over Output generated through use of the Work.

(b) Licensee Input. Licensee and Licensee's users retain all rights, title, and interest in Licensee Input. Nothing in this Agreement transfers ownership of Licensee Input to Licensor.

(c) Third-Party Rights. This Agreement does not grant any rights in third-party content, data, software, models, datasets, trademarks, or other materials that are not owned or controlled by Licensor.

(d) Output Responsibility. Licensee is solely responsible for determining whether its use, publication, distribution, or commercialization of Output complies with applicable law and third-party rights.


