8. TERMINATION AND REINSTATEMENT

(a) Automatic Termination for Breach. Any material breach of this Agreement automatically terminates the rights granted to Licensee under this Agreement.

(b) Cure and Reinstatement. If Licensee cures the breach within thirty (30) days after becoming aware of the breach or receiving notice of the breach, the rights granted under this Agreement are reinstated prospectively.

(c) Permanent Termination for Repeated or Uncured Breach. If Licensee fails to cure a material breach within the cure period, or repeatedly breaches this Agreement after prior notice, Licensor may permanently terminate Licensee's rights under this Agreement.

(d) Downstream Recipients. Termination of Licensee's rights does not automatically terminate the rights of downstream recipients who received the Work or Covered Work from Licensee and who remain in compliance with this Agreement.

(e) No Arbitrary Revocation. Licensor and Project Maintainer may not revoke rights granted under this Agreement except as provided in this Section.


